parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls while driving
the transmission slips or shudders
the RPMs fluctuate rapidly
the vehicle loses power
the accelerator pedal is unresponsive
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward
the transmission makes grinding noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and shuddering can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or shudders
the vehicle hesitates or stalls while driving
the RPMs fluctuate rapidly
the vehicle loses power
the accelerator pedal is unresponsive
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure without warning can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
hesitates
or stalls while driving without any warning lights or indicators
the transmission fails without any prior symptoms.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the push-button start fails
the battery drains quickly
the horn is not loud enough
and the air conditioning shuts off while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
the transmission slips
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels stiff or hard
the brake switch acts up
and the vehicle won't start due to brake pedal issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
and the airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The parasitic battery drain can cause the battery to drain quickly, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery drains quickly
and the vehicle requires continuous jump starts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to stall or not shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle is severely damaged
and occupants are injured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning airbag sensor can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light is always on
airbag sensor malfunctions inconsistently
passenger airbag light is on even when the seat is occupied
and the system works properly at times but not always.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or incomplete repairs of airbag recalls can leave vehicles with faulty airbags, putting occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Dealers fail to replace airbags
parts are unavailable for repair
and manufacturers mislead the public about the availability of repairs.
